  "title": "Osteopath",
  "description": "<p><br></p>\n<p>· <strong>Patient Assessment:</strong> Conduct comprehensive assessments of patients' health, including physical examinations, medical history reviews, and TCM diagnostic techniques.</p>\n<p>· <strong>Treatment Planning:</strong> Develop individualized treatment plans based on TCM principles and osteopathic techniques to address patients' specific health concerns.</p>\n<p>· <strong>Manual Manipulation:</strong> Utilize osteopathic manual manipulation techniques to address musculoskeletal issues, improve circulation, and alleviate pain</p>\n<p>· <strong>Dietary and Lifestyle Recommendations:</strong> Provide guidance on dietary modifications and lifestyle changes to support patients' overall health and well-being.</p>\n<p>· <strong>Education and Counseling</strong>: Educate patients about TCM principles, treatment options, and self-care strategies to empower them in managing their health.</p>\n<p>· <strong>Record Keeping:</strong> Maintain accurate and confidential patient records, including treatment plans, progress notes, recommendations and purchases.</p>\n<p>· <strong>Inventory:</strong> To ensure sufficient inventories and quantities of products and medicines with proper storage and maintenance.</p>\n<p>· <strong>Collaboration:</strong> Work with TCM Physicians and front-liners to ensure comprehensive patient care.</p>\n<p>· <strong>Events and Activities:</strong> Participate in all marketing initiatives, promotional road shows, trade fairs, corporate events, demonstration programs, health talks and any events. Internally and externally.</p>",
